==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Terbium
<hw>Ter"bi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Yt<ets>terby</ets>, in Sweden. See <er>Erbium</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare metallic element, found in certain
minerals, as gadolinite and samarskite, with other rare earths such as
ytterbium. Symbol Tb. Atomic number 65. Atomic weight 158.925.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

